
setUp().details: Initializes the contract with a default metadata URI.

testContractURIAccessControl().details: Expects revert with OwnableUnauthorizedAccount when called by unauthorized user.

testContractURIChange().details: Verifies getter reflects the new value after update.

testCreatePolisAndGetUnity().details: Verifies that each Polis correctly stores the assigned parent Unity ID.

testOikosListFiltering().details: Creates tokens with varying statuses and verifies correct inclusion/exclusion in the result array.

testSetParentUnity().details: Verifies that the change is stored and can be read back.

setUp().notice: Sets up a fresh Polis instance before each test.

testContractURIAccessControl().notice: Tests that only the contract owner can update the contract URI.

testContractURIChange().notice: Tests that contract URI can be updated by the owner.

testCreatePolisAndGetUnity().notice: Tests creation of multiple Polises and retrieval of their Unity values.

testEmit_ContractURIUpdatedEvent().notice: Tests that ContractURIUpdated event is emitted on change.

testEmit_NewPolisEvent().notice: Tests that NewPolis event is emitted correctly.

testEmit_ParentUnityChangeEvent().notice: Tests that ParentUnityChanging event is emitted on change.

testGetOikosListEmptyResult().notice: Tests getOikosList when there are no matching Oikos tokens.

testGetOikosListInvalidStatusRange().notice: Tests getOikosList with invalid status range (min > max).

testGetOikosListLimitExceedsMatches().notice: Tests getOikosList when requested number exceeds actual matches.

testOikosListFiltering().notice: Tests filtering of Oikos tokens within a given Polis by status range.

testParentUnityOverwrites().notice: Tests overwriting parent unity of a Polis multiple times.

testSetParentUnity().notice: Tests updating the Unity of an existing Polis.

testStatusNumUpdate().notice: Tests that statusNum can be updated by owner.
